>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Hook Words Complete Guide ŌĆö Front and Back Hooks","description":"Complete guide to hook words in Scrabble. Front hooks, back hooks, profitable extensions, and strategic hook plays.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-hook-words-complete-guide"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is a hook word in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A hook word is formed by adding a single letter to the front or back of an existing word on the board. For example, adding S to CARE makes CARES (back hook), or adding S to LAUGHTER makes SLAUGHTER (front hook)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the most profitable hook letters?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"S is the most valuable hook letter ŌĆö it pluralises most nouns. Other profitable hooks: E (back hook for -ED/-ER forms), D (past tense), R (comparative), and Y (adjective forms). Front hooks like B, C, P, T transform many words."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you set up hook plays?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Play words that leave hookable endings near premium squares. Place CARE so adding S lands on a triple-word square. Your opponent either blocks it or leaves it open for your 30+ point hook play."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">ŌåÉ Blog</a><span class="mx-1">ŌĆ║</span><span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Hook Words Complete Guide ŌĆö Front & Back Hooks</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>6 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">­¤öż</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Hook words are the bread and butter of strategic Scrabble. By adding a single letter to an existing word, you score both your new word AND re-score the extended word ŌĆö often landing on premium squares. Mastering hooks separates club players from casual ones.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2 words</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Scored per hook</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">S tile</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Most valuable hook</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">80%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Words hookable</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3x</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Score on TWS</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Back Hooks ŌĆö Adding to the End</h2>
      <p>Back hooks add a letter to the end of an existing word ŌĆö the most common and intuitive hooks:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">+S (Plural/Verb)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CAREŌåÆCARES, RUNŌåÆRUNS. Works on ~70% of words. Save S tiles for hooks.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">+D/+ED (Past Tense)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PLAYŌåÆPLAYED, CAREŌåÆCARED. Creates 6-7 letter words from common bases.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">+R/+ER (Comparative)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FASTŌåÆFASTER, HIGHŌåÆHIGHER. Good for rack-clearing plays.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">+Y (Adjective)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">RAINŌåÆRAINY, SALTŌåÆSALTY. Y=4 adds scoring power to the extension.</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Front Hooks ŌĆö Adding to the Start</h2>
      <p>Front hooks are less obvious and more powerful ŌĆö opponents often miss them:</p>
